;;; ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;;; PART 1: THE ABSTRACT — WHAT CHARLOTTE IS
;;; ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

(isa CharlotteSubstrate Collection)
(genls CharlotteSubstrate PROTOCOL)
(comment CharlotteSubstrate
  "Charlotte is the first layer of an infinite stack of operating systems.
   Every business that wants to be a business gets its own OS — custom-compiled
   to its own operations, its own vocabulary, its own rhythm. A pig farm runs
   on a different instruction set than a violin dealer, which runs on a
   different instruction set than a moving company. But because every OS is
   built on top of Charlotte, they are all interoperable by construction.
   They can all talk to each other. They can all learn from each other.
   The kernel never changes.

   Charlotte is the universal layer: five primitives — Node, Edge, Metric,
   Signal, Protocol — and a temporal spine running from epoch to millisecond.
   The observer lives on this spine in Kd-space, placing signals on metric
   lines. Each domain OS stacked on top shrinks the convex hull of the
   knowledge space — restricting the vocabulary, tightening the instruction
   set, compiling a full end-to-end pipeline into the smallest possible
   encoding for that specific business.

   Layer 1 is universal. Layer N is bespoke. Every layer in between is just
   a tighter ontology.

   The result is not one product. It is an infinite number of products — each
   one custom, each one small enough to be invisible, each one powerful enough
   to run an entire operation — all stacked on the same kernel, all sharing
   the same temporal spine, all speaking the same language at the bottom.

   The correct measure of technological progress is not how much technology
   people use. It is how little they notice.")


