;;; ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
;;; PART 3: THE 97% THESIS
;;; ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

(isa NinetySeven Collection)
(genls NinetySeven NODE)
(comment NinetySeven
  "The 97% Thesis: there are 33.2 million small businesses in the United
   States. 97% were built before AI existed. Most predate broadband internet.
   Many predate the personal computer. These businesses — corner-store
   libraries, family coffee shops, third-generation hardware stores — do not
   need more technology. They need the complexity of modernity to stop
   eroding them while they do what they were built to do.

   Charlotte is titanium injected directly into the bone. The business does
   not change. The owner learns nothing new. No new screens. No new logins.
   No training. No migration. The substrate observes the signals the business
   already emits — transactions, schedules, inventory, deliveries — and
   converts them into structural intelligence. Devices manage themselves.
   The infrastructure thinks so the owner does not have to.

   The endgame is not a world with more technology everywhere. It is a world
   with less visible technology and more underlying intelligence.")


