(isa AbsorptionModel Collection)
(genls AbsorptionModel PROTOCOL)
(comment AbsorptionModel
  "The technology industry built one-size-fits-all software for the 3% of
   businesses born digital. Charlotte builds an infinite number of bespoke
   operating systems for the other 97%. Each business gets its own OS —
   compiled from its own signals, shrunk to its own instruction set —
   without knowing it exists.

   The adoption tax disappears because there is nothing to adopt. The
   infrastructure observes what the business already does and compiles
   itself around it.

   At 1% penetration of American small businesses paying $1K-$10K/month
   for invisible infrastructure, the market generates $6B ARR — exceeding
   Palantir, Snowflake, and MongoDB.")


